        "body": "Thanks for pointing me to the community repository. I'll definitely keep an eye on it.\r\n\r\nTo create a GitHub Release that can be watched, you could add a curl POST to the GitHub REST API to your release procedure. For example the following\r\n```\r\ncurl -v -i -X POST -H \"Content-Type:application/json\" -u joschaschmiedt:1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1 https://api.github.com/repos/joschaschmiedt/dask/releases -d '{\"tag_name\":\"2.4.0\",\"target_commitish\": \"master\",\"name\": \"2.4.0\",\"body\": \"See https://docs.dask.org/en/latest/changelog.html\",\"draft\": false,\"prerelease\": false}'\r\n```\r\nwill result in something like [this](https://github.com/joschaschmiedt/dask/releases/tag/2.4.0). It requires an access token with the appropriate scope.\r\n",
