        "body": "You could also use a service like [IFTTT to send you emails when a new RSS item is added](https://ifttt.com/applets/147561p-rss-feed-to-email).\r\n\r\n> Another option would be to manually create a release from a tag via the GitHub web interface\r\n\r\nThis is definitely a common pattern. But so is updating a changelog file, creating a git tag and pushing it. I'm not sure changing the convention here is going to be that helpful.\r\n\r\nOne option would be to add a CI/CD step to run your curl command when a tagged commit is created. We could potentially also take the relevant section from the changelog, run it through a rst to md converter and include that in the release.",
